	<Title>
		Recipe: Cranberry orange glaze
	</Title>
	<Abstract />
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Cranberries, also known as bounceberries because ripe cranberries bounce, are high in vitamin C. One serving of this recipe provides about 40 percent of most people&apos;s daily needs for vitamin C.&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;In a microwaveable bowl, combine the cranberries, orange juice and cornstarch. Stir well. Microwave on high until the mixture thickens, about 3 to 4 minutes. Stir several times during cooking. Set aside to cool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add the sugar substitute to taste, equivalent of 1 teaspoon sugar. The glaze should be tart. Serve over chicken, turkey or pork. This is also an excellent sauce for grilling, roasting or using as a marinade.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;p&gt;1 cup fresh cranberries, chopped&lt;br /&gt;
2/3 cup unsweetened orange juice&lt;br /&gt;
1 tablespoon cornstarch&lt;br /&gt;
Sugar substitute, to taste&lt;/p&gt;
	</Ingredients>
